<paragraph blockId="6.[175,1005,1095,1355]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">
The 
<typeStatus box="[243,330,1228,1249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">lectotype</typeStatus>
(SBL 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[391,409,1228,1248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">¼</emphasis>
<quantity box="[414,490,1228,1249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" unit="mm" value="6.1">6.1 mm</quantity>
; ABL 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[552,570,1228,1248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">¼</emphasis>
about 
<quantity box="[634,708,1228,1249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
) is conspecific with specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Allen, 1972" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1972" box="[203,424,1254,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitiosus">
<emphasis box="[203,302,1254,1275]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">L. vitiosus</emphasis>
Allen, 1972
</taxonomicName>
[
<subScript attach="left" box="[439,478,1260,1274]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">NEW</subScript>
SYNONYMY]. The species is structurally very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wright" authorityName="Wright" authorityYear="1939" box="[175,329,1281,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duryi">
<emphasis box="[175,253,1281,1302]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">L. duryi</emphasis>
Wright
</taxonomicName>
but the mentum foveal pits are smaller, the shapes of the pronotum and of the median lobe of the aedeagus differ in minute details, and the endophallic structures are differently arranged.
</paragraph>
